snippet.textDisplay: SO Excited! This theme of “Home” couldn’t have been any more appropriate for me. I arrived back to my “physical” home in the USA yesterday after a year+ of international travel (YWA went all over the world with me, (Mexico, China, South Korea, India, The Philippines, Thailand...) and kept me feeling connected and grounded in many new environments, and on many many rough days. I am so THANKFUL for this community, and the encouragement, positivity, and reflection that it facilitates!! 2020 HERE WE COME! Looking forward to a month solid of support as I settle back and reconnect to my “home”, inside and out. 🥰🧘‍♀️🏠 Love to you all out there!

snippet.textDisplay:
In 2019, i continuously started and stopped my yoga journey because I always thought I was too busy to be able to fit it in anywhere but now that I look back, there was so much time I had where I could fit in maybe a 30 minute session. Now I’m not beating myself up over it because this year, starting today, I’m going to make it habit to wake up and do some yoga to start my day with a peaceful mindset. And I’m so beyond grateful that you, Adriene, are going to be the one leading me through it!
Also, not gonna lie, I cried a little bit watching this video because I do need healing within myself and it was nice to hear I’m not alone here (something I need to remember more often). So thank you for creating such an inviting and warm place to be. I look forward to spending this year with you and everyone else here!

snippet.textDisplay:
Last year I was sitting on my floor watching Dedicate's orientation video with a bit of hesitation that could I even do this but with more determination to "show up for myself" everyday for 30 days. I was focused on doing something just for me and my health ( self care). I figured if nothing else I'd get a good stretch everyday.
Today as I watched Home's orientation video I had tears of joy streaming down my face. You see in 2019 not only did I complete Dedicate but also every calendar for the whole year. I not only surpassed my original goal but surprised myself with finishing out the year. Life has been so hard for quite some time now and for the first time in a very long time I can't wait to start a new year. I know that this community Adriene, Benji and all of you have helped me heal and find joy again. thank y'all from the bottom of my heart. SEE Y'ALL ON THE MAT! Namaste!!!!!

I couldn't really practice with Adriene for the past few months because many things happened and I wasn't ready to face my emotions. But maybe this is a good time. I hope it is. I expect many tears but it will help me to heal.
I believe we can do it all together. It's the beginning of an amazing journey.

snippet.textDisplay: I am so looking forward to this. I'm not exaggerating when I say that Dedicate helped save my life last year. While some aspects of my life have improved since then, I'm still in a pretty sad, dark space. That said, I also have more faith and confidence and determination than I've felt in a long time that in 2020, I will turn things around for myself, manifest some magic, make every effort to live more fully, get out of these dreary ruts, and, well, find my way home. snippet.textDisplay: Hi Adriene I'm a construction guy and gym rat for nearly 30 years. I found my flexibility and years of micro injuries from work and the gym taking its tole in the form of minor arthritis and loss of flexibility. In late 2019 I worked through your 30 Days and was completely blown away by the breathing relaxation calming and physical effects. My flexibility and strength have increased my inflammation has dramatically decreased and I feel like a different person. I thought I was in pretty good shape (not at all) until I tried your Yoga...mind blowing awakening and life changing...thanks you so much! I have started hot yoga at a local studio (Oxygen) and love it. I thank you, think your amazing, love your style personality (keep doing you) and cant wait to get started on the 2020 30 Days. The braids look great haha Cheers! Troy

snippet.textOriginal: This will be my third January with you, and I’m grateful for what you bring each year and put out into the world all year long.

snippet.textDisplay: What moves me most here is us -- collectively and all over this tiny blue planet we call home. Makes my intention to show up -- here and in life -- more powerful. Strength in numbers. Thank you all for being here today and in the days ahead. Namaste.
